author: National Geographic
description:
Wildlife biologist and Nat Geo Explorer Liz Bonnin visits the Galápagos on a National Geographic-Lindblad Expeditions cruise uncovering the islands' incredible wildlife—she encounters ancient tortoises, playful seabirds with different colored feet, and a heart-warming sea lion pup. From Darwin’s finches to wave-battling marine iguanas, this is a magical journey where discovery in the Galápagos never stops.

Learn how to join a National Geographic Expedition at https://www.nationalgeographic.com/expeditions/trip-search/galapagos-expedition-cruise-trips/
